# Testing Guidelines

kheMessage uses manual testing due to its single-file architecture.

## Testing Checklist

### Core Features

1. **Editor**
   - [ ] Type text and verify it appears
   - [ ] Markdown renders correctly (headers, bold, italic, code)
   - [ ] Undo/redo works (Ctrl+Z, Ctrl+Y)
   - [ ] Content persists on page refresh

2. **URL Storage**
   - [ ] URL hash updates when content changes
   - [ ] Opening URL loads content correctly
   - [ ] Special characters work (emoji, unicode)
   - [ ] Long content doesn't exceed URL limits

3. **Version History**
   - [ ] Versions appear in history dropdown
   - [ ] Version undo/redo works
   - [ ] Preview mode shows old version
   - [ ] Restore version works
   - [ ] Reset clears history

4. **Theme**
   - [ ] Toggle switches between light/dark
   - [ ] URL parameter (`?theme=dark`) works
   - [ ] System preference respected
   - [ ] All UI elements adapt

5. **Share**
   - [ ] Copy link copies to clipboard
   - [ ] Export TXT downloads text file
   - [ ] Export HTML downloads styled HTML
   - [ ] Export MD downloads markdown

6. **QR Code**
   - [ ] QR code renders in panel
   - [ ] QR code updates with URL
   - [ ] Full-page QR works (/qr)

7. **PWA**
   - [ ] App is installable
   - [ ] Works offline after install
   - [ ] Service worker caches assets

## Browser Testing

Test in these browsers:
- Chrome (latest)
- Firefox (latest)
- Safari (latest)
- Edge (latest)
- Mobile Safari
- Mobile Chrome

## Edge Cases

- Empty document
- Single character
- Maximum length content
- Content with only special characters
- Rapid consecutive saves
- Multiple tabs with same content
